race.comment: DISTINCTLY SUMMER (9) broke her maiden last start at Echuca with a good win, well supported into $2.70 and leading throughout there after showing speed in the small field. She's tactically versatile and has a bit more upside than most of these. She'll just need a good ride from the draw to be winning again. MARTY MCFLY (4) is another coming off a maiden win, doing it easily at Hamilton as the $2.15 favourite last time out. He sets up nicely from the gate for Riordan and looks to have come back much better. SIMPLY LUSCIOUS (6) is knocking on the door with consecutive minor placings. She's speedy and will be in this for a long way. SCREAM (8) is third up and ready to fire off a solid run at Mornington while EPIC CENTRE (1) has the class to win this and will be fitter.
